==English==

===Etymology===

From the Latin trans meaning across and the Latin lucet meaning it is light.

===Adjective===
'''translucent''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''more translucent''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''most translucent''')

#allowing [[light]] to pass through but [[scatter]]ing it as it does, to give [[diffuse]] [[image]]s
#[[clear]] or [[lucid]]
:One could say that [[salivae]] is a '''translucent''' goo.

